Fig. 6c showed a better linear relationship (R2=0.996) of Hg2+ concentration and PL intensity with the concentration range from 0-30 μM. The estimation for limit of detection (LOD) was 0.25 nM equal to three times the standard deviation rule (LOD=3Sd/s, n=7). It was significantly smaller than those found with other carbon based fluorescent probes (
Table 2
). Compared with the other fluorescent sensors for detecting Hg2+, Table 2 clearly showed that the N-GQDs synthesized through the proposed method achieved a relatively low detection limit of Hg2+, as well as a relatively wide linear range. In brief, the effectiveness and value of N-GQDs as a fluorescent sensor were strongly confirmed.
